<div align="center"><h2>Welcome to Everquest Online</h2></div><br />
<b>Everquest Online</b> is a fan site with plenty of information about the online MMORPG from Sony: <i>Everquest</i>.<br />
<br />
<i>Everquest</i> is the largest online roleplaying game to date with over 400,000 subscribers world-wide, 6 expansions, over 40 servers, and fan fairs with the most active and close-knit community around.<br />
<br />
The multitude of activities you can do in Everquest are:<ul><li>Choose from 15 different and unique races</li><li>Become one of 16 different classes, each with their own skills and abilities</li><li>Fight in large scale battles</li><li>Defeat enormous monsters</li><li>Buy and Sell to become a wealthy merchant</li><li>Join parties and groups to go hunting and questing with</li><li>Collect thousands of items</li><li>Learn thousands of spells to cast</li></ul>
<hr><br />
<h2>Announcement: Submit Your Everquest Guide!</h2>&nbsp;posted&nbsp;Sunday, July 25, 2004 9:57 AM EDT (  <a href="http://www.everquest-online.com/cgi-bin/admin/printnews.cgi?newsid1090767465,499," target="_blank"><img src="http://www.everquest-online.com/content/templates/1/images/print.gif" height="11" width="15" border="0" alt="Printer Friendly Page" /></a> <a href="http://www.everquest-online.com/cgi-bin/admin/sendnews.cgi?newsid1090767465,499," target="_blank"><img src="http://www.everquest-online.com/content/templates/1/images/mail.gif" height="11" width="15" border="0" alt="Send this Article to a Friend" /></a> )<br />You can now submit your <b>EQ Guide</b> to us on our <a href="http://www.everquest-online.com/content/everquest-addguide.php" class="newslink">Add Guide page</a>. Special rewards for unique and thorough guides. Please submit your personal work only, do not copy someone else's guide.<br /><br /><div align="center"><h1>EQ Everquest News</h1></div>
<br />
<h2>Mobhunter News</h2>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<i>Monday December 6, 2004</i><br />News of the Winter's Moon by Loral on 4 December 2004 : This week we look at the state of the game this holiday season and make a few wild and uninformed predictions. We also take a look at what we hope to see in the coming December 15th patch. - 0 Comments Where's my pop-tart...&nbsp;<a href="http://mobhunter.com/" target="_blank">[read more]</a><br /><br /><h2>EQ2 Casters Realm News</h2>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<i>Monday December 6, 2004</i><br />Monday, December 6, 2004 BETRAYAL GUIDE GOOD TO EVIL Want to get in touch with your darker side Fureya can help you She has written a very comprehensive guide on how to betray the city of Qeynos to join Freeport. Read her guide here or visit the playing guides section . Submitted by Gemdiver , 06:13 PST Saturday, December 4, 2004 PATCH NOTES - DEC 3 Dec 3 Patch Notes available here. Submitted by Gemdiver , 08:23 PST Thursday, December 2, 2004 HEROIC OPPORTUNITIES GUIDE This week, Ikikgud gives...&nbsp;<a href="http://eq2.crgaming.com/" target="_blank">[read more]</a><br /><br /><h2>Planet EQ News</h2>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<i>Monday December 6, 2004</i><br />EQLive Splitpaw Revamp 12/6/04, 11:36 PST Kwill Zone Revamp - Splitpaw Re-vamped Splitpaw hits Legends on December 15th and will be available to all the other servers in January. Farsoth Mal, son of the Ishva Mal, leader of the Verishe Mal tribe, sat by his father's side watching him rule his minions in Splitpaw Lair. His father may have conquered this lair some years ago, but Farsoth believed they should rule far more than just one underground kingdom. He grew to despise his father for his lac...&nbsp;<a href="http://www.planeteq.com/" target="_blank">[read more]</a><br /><br /><h2>EQ2 Vault News</h2>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<i>Monday December 6, 2004</i><br />Mon 06 Dec 2004 EQII VN Board - Helpful Hints Contest Post A Comment - Print News Mail News Kestrel has started a contest on the boards in relation to a very good helpful hints write-up on the official boards, you can view the details here . This thread is for the EQ2 Community to pass on helpful hints in EQ2 to enrich your gaming experience. The original information came from Tarindel, posting on the Official Boards. His thread can be found here . Thanks to aeiou-y for sharing it here. Feel fr...&nbsp;<a href="http://eq2vault.ign.com/" target="_blank">[read more]</a><br /><br /><h2>EQ2 Stratics News</h2>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<i>Monday December 6, 2004</i><br />Monday December 6 2004 Good news Brawlers Brawler News - 7:56 AM EST Posted By: Sylvene The Brawler Deflection Bug was fixed with Saturday's update. This was the first item in the Update Notes. The Deflection skill should now be working properly for brawlers, monks, and bruisers. Visit Our Forums All English Language Servers Down Again. EQII Updates - 7:54 AM EST Posted By: Sylvene The almost daily updates continue as all English Language servers come down today at 7am PST for approximately one...&nbsp;<a href="http://eq2.stratics.com/" target="_blank">[read more]</a><br /><br /><h2>EQ Casters Realm News</h2>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<i>Monday December 6, 2004</i><br />Monday, December 6, 2004 PLANES OF PARODY, EPISODE I A while ago, Sam Smith wrote a great parody on the Planes of Power called The Planes of Parody. It will make any visitor to the planes laugh for sure. Read Planes of Parody, Episode I here. Submitted by Gemdiver , 01:03 PST Friday, December 3, 2004 HOW TO WRITE FAN FICTION Loral Ciriclight is one of the most well known fan fiction writers for EverQuest. This week he writes an article for any aspiring fan fiction writers for the Do s and Do No...&nbsp;<a href="http://eq.crgaming.com/" target="_blank">[read more]</a><br /><br /><h2>Township Rebellion News</h2>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<i>Monday December 6, 2004</i><br />Ture falls again Posted by adetia on December 5, 2004 at 20:53 EST You gotta love it when a plan comes together This week's agenda has been trial backflagging, a smattering of Epic 2.0 fights, and frequent trips to Anguish including a rematch against Ture Congrats to our recent loot winners: Valero, Abasio, Darkoor, Dakora, Kalamaku, Baliel, Ibew, Nandari, Dalwhinnie, Lynnhart, Kijari, Pinene, Loofy, Kinvaras, Angelcat, Soram, Xphobe, Vigilyn, Quoits, Chantzir, and Ragey Its been a busy few day...&nbsp;<a href="http://www.townrebels.org/" target="_blank">[read more]</a><br /><br /><h2>EQlizer News</h2>&nbsp;-&nbsp;<i>Monday December 6, 2004</i><br />alt 2004-12-05 Weekend Update Posted by : J.C. Smith This weekend update features an assortment of items, with highlights coming from Veeshan's Peak. Part of this update came in on Friday but somehow the news post got borked, so you get two updates in one here. New Equipment: Radiant Skyflow of Minor Ferocity Radiant Skyflow of Minor Dexterity Radiant Skyflow of Pure Aggression Radiant Skyflow of Pure Haste Radiant Skyflow of Efficiency Aged Sarnak Channeler Staff Aged Left Eye of Xygoz Reincor...&nbsp;<a href="http://eqlizer.net/index.shtml" target="_blank">[read more]</a><br /><br /><br /><br /><b><a href="http://wetrack.it/yantis/af.cgi?aid=919&redirect=http://www.mysupersales.com/">MySuperSales</a> is the best place for the cheapest Platinum and top items at the lowest prices</b>
